  label="Base Trace: Question: Given a 15.00 kg body accelerated by 75.00 N from rest, calculate the distance traveled in 7.000 seconds. Answer (step-by-step): 1. Calculate the acceleration of the body using the formula a = F / m, where F is the force applied and m is the mass of the body. 2. Substitute the given values into the formula: a = 75.00 N / 15.00 kg = 5.00 m/s^2. 3. Use the formula for distance traveled under constant acceleration: d = 0.5 * a * t^2, where d is the distance, a is the acceleration, and t is the time. 4. Substitute the given values into the formula: d = 0.5 * 5.00 m/s^2 * (7.000 s)^2 = 0....\n\n                  v26                          v25                                                   v24                                   v23                                                                                                                                v22                                                  v21       v20        v19      v18v17                                                                       v16         v15                                                                   v14                                                  v13   v12      v11  v10      v9  v8    v7       v6  v5       v4  v3        v2                                      v1               v0";
